Ext.data.JsonP['AMPLIFY_Appcelerator_Services']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>AMPLIFY Appcelerator Services</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-43298711\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>AMPLIFY Appcelerator Services</h1>\n    <p>    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n            <p>Appcelerator Platform is available as a service referred as App Builder through the AMPLIFY(<sup class=\" \">TM</sup>) platform.    </p>\n    </div>\n        <p>    </p>\n    <p>Appcelerator Services are a set of features that include:    </p>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p><strong class=\" \">Appcelerator Test</strong>: Integrated automated functional testing for your application allowing developers and testers to collaborate on recording tests directly on the mobile device, executing tests and analyzing the results.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><strong class=\" \">Appcelerator Performance</strong>: Monitor your application&apos;s health, crashes and overall performance to help developers diagnose why applications crash and focus on specific issues based on user feedback.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><strong class=\" \">Appcelerator Analytics</strong>: Track your applications&apos; user adoption and engagement to help understand how your application is used, which features are not used and decide what will go in the next version of your application.    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>For Titanium applications, activate the services using Appcelerator Studio, which enables basic analytics and performance data collection.  For advanced features, you need to add Titanium API calls to the application.    </p>\n    <p>For native Android applications built with Java and iOS applications built with Objective-C, use the <a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Managing_Non-Titanium_Client_Applications_in_Dashboard\">Dashboard to activate Appcelerator Services</a> and the <a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/AMPLIFY_Appcelerator_Services_Native_SDKs\">AMPLIFY Appcelerator Services Native SDKs</a> to integrate the services with the application.    </p>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=43298711\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"AMPLIFY Appcelerator Services"});